Usage: deleteIntegRouteConstraint [-help] {-net <net1 net2 ...> | -name <string> | -customConstraints  | -all  | -additional }

-help                    # Prints out the command usage
-additional              # Removes additionalConstraint file from memory.
                         # (bool, required)
-all                     # Deletes all integration constraints including those
                         # constraints understood by NR. (bool, required)
-customConstraints       # Tells the command to delete all diffpair, match,
                         # complex shield and complex netclass constraints.
                         # (bool, required)
-name <string>           # This option allows the deletion of a specific
                         # constraint by name. The user can use the
                         # getIntegRouteConstraint command in order to get the
                         # name of any constraint in the design.
                         # (string, required)
-net <net1 net2 ...>     # Indicates the nets for which the constraints will be
                         # deleted. If the net part of a netClass, the netClass
                         # will be deleted as well. (string, required)